              adductors, diductors, dorsal and ventral pedicle adjustors,
              mantle margin muscles, a distinct musculature of the intestine,
              and striated muscle fibres in the tentacles for all three
              species. CONCLUSION: Our data indicate that larvae of
              rhynchonelliform brachiopods share a common muscular bodyplan and
              are thus derived from a common ancestral larval type. Comparison
              of the muscular phenotype of rhynchonelliform larvae to that of
              the other two lophophorate phyla, Phoronida and Ectoprocta, does
