              germ layers during metazoan evolution are unknown. But an
              increased understanding of development in early diverging taxa at
              the base of the metazoan tree may provide insights into the
              origins of these developmental mechanisms. RESULTS: In the
              anthozoan cnidarian Nematostella vectensis, initial archenteron
